e he understood for the first time what it was that artists spoke about when they spoke of beauty.\n\n- Ayn Rand, The Fountainhead\n|\nNever respond to an angry person with a fiery comeback, even if he deserves it...Don't allow his anger to become your anger.\n\n- Bohdi Sanders, Warrior Wisdom: Ageless Wisdom for the Modern Warrior\n|\nRespect towards humanity may get weaken when it comes about Stomach, Shelter and Sleep\n\n- Samar\n|\nWe may place blame, give reasons, and even have excuses; but in the end, it is an act of cowardice to not follow your dreams.\n\n- Steve\n|\nYou must write as if Dostoyevsky himself will be reading your novel, and Shakespeare will be acting it out.\n\n- Christina Westover, Precipice\n|\nOnly a sense of lightness, giddy and dizzying, like flight—of a burden that didn't belong to me being lifted.Suddenly I knew the truth and the lights surrounding me exp\n\n- Andrea Cremer, Bloodrose\n|\nSaturday night is perfect for writers because other people have 'plans.\n\n- Mike\n|\nYour dreams are the golden gate to a life of inspiration. The more you allow yourself to dream of your ideal future, the stronger your inspiration.\n\n- Mensah\n|\n...the desert is so huge, and the horizons so distant, that they make a person feel small, and as if he should remain silent.\n\n- Paulo\n|\nNature hath no goal, though she hath law.\n\n- John\n|\nBetrayal and dishonor is usually an inside job. Keep it 'sucka-free', loved one!\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nThough wrong gratifies in the moment, good yields its gifts over a lifetime.\n\n- Desmond\n|\nIf a man will begin with certainties, he shall end in doubts; but if he will be content to begin with doubts, he shall end in certainties.\n\n- Francis Bacon, The Advancement Of Learning\n|\nWhile the whole world was asleep, the caterpillar was awake, working towards becoming a butterfly.\n\n- Matshona\n|\n...when dogma ent